title: For Sale:  1972 Remington 700 7mm Magnum
postcontent: Purchased rifle to use the receiver in a magnum build I am doing, but have decided to use a different rifle for historical accuracy reasons. From what I can tell, the rifle was made in January of 1972 based on the barrel stamps and lack of alphabetical prefix in front of the serial number like on newer rifles. The rifle is in very good condition given its age, but it does have some minor scratches on the stock. No cracks or major damage though. The rifle I decided to use is not in as good of condition as this one even though it is about 10 years newer.This rifle has a 24" barrel with blade sights, chambered in 7mm Magnum with a twist rate of either 1:9 or 1:10. The trigger has been worked over / polished and has a pull of maybe 1.5 pounds. It is a rather light trigger, but the pull is nice and tight with no creep or slack at all. Despite the light pull, you need to pull directly in the middle of the trigger and it is difficult to set off by just pulling the edges - this means there is little chance of accidently bumping it. A vintage 2-7x Redfield Widefield rifle scope is currently mounted on the gun as well and is included. I paid exactly $575 for this rifle and I am just looking to get my money back out of it. If you were to part the rifle out. the barrel is worth $75+, the scope is about $120, the original stock given its condition is around $80, and then the action (receiver, bolt, trigger) is worth $375 give or take some. Recoil lug and bottom floor metal are also worth some money. This is cool old gun that has clearly been cared for and not abused, hence the reason I bought it and why I was hesitant enough to not rip it apart for my build. 7mm is also a power house of a round. At 3,000 fps at the muzzle, even with light hunting charges, this gun will drop any animal in the state with ease. Please email, I will be out of town from July 1 to 21, but will make arrangements for anyone interested in the gun for when I return. If the ad is up, the gun is available.

title: For Sale:  New Version of the Army Duffel Bag
postcontent: For sale is a US Army issue duffel bag. These have a full-length double zipper that allows one to access the whole bag. For anyone who has used an Army duffel, there are times where what you need is at the bottom of the duffel, and essentially one has to dump the whole duffel to be able to get at it. These duffels don't have that problem, you can unzip the bag to see what is in it from top to bottom. However, the hasp where you can put a lock to prevent others from getting into the bag is retained and the zips can be situated so that they are under the hasp when closed. Also, these duffels have backpack straps, just like the old ones, so that the bag can be carried on the back. There are also handles on both ends for pulling the bag in and out of storage and a handle on the top for carrying with one hand. On one side of the bag there is a clear document holder that can be used to slip in either the name of the owner, or perhaps the contents of the bag. Essentially one can put whatever one wants in the document holder, presumably to idenfity the owner or contents of the bag.  Can ship for $5.  This bag is new, but may show some storage marks from being in a tote. It originated with the US government, and is the same bag that they sell at AAFES clothing and sales for $40. I have more pictures if needed.If you see the ad, the items are availible.  Queries such as "Is this still availible," will be treated as attemps to phish my e-mail and ignored.
